ADB pushes Asia for help in the rescue of the eurozone
The developing bank of Asia (Asian Development bank, ADB) calls on India and China to support the rescue of the eurozone in his heavy debt crisis to prevent a long-term downward trend which will brake the growth of the economy of Asia.
Rajat Gnawing, administrative manager of the ADB with headquarter in Manila, said that both fastest growing economic nations of the world must do "everything in your power standing" to accelerate the rest of the currency block either by the international currency ground or by direct mutual arrangements.
He warned about the BRIC countries (Brazil, Russia, India, China) which look "without passion" at the difficulties in Europe, and said that the financial support of the European guidance and the European resources helps to prevent a long-term breakdown of the global economy through Asia.
"We sit everybody in the same boat."
"Everybody is helpful which can help Europe from this crisis", he said the Financial Times during an interview on the edge of the world economy forum in Mumbai.
"Asia may be protected up to a certain degree, but it is not immune."
"If China and India can help, then with all means."
Monetary union of Europe got during the past months in a heavy debt crisis.
During the past days interest costs of Italy rose dangerously and the prime ministers from Italy as well as from Greece have withdrawn.
The upcoming heavy debt crisis in Europe pokes fears that the global economy could fall in the recession and led to calls, the leading threshold countries would have to get together to support the eurozone.
