Anand Sharma, the Indian Secretary of Commerce, said that "India does everything what stands in his power" to help the eurozone, because own economy suffers now from the sinking exports and drying up foreign capital flow.
"Nobody wants that the eurozone remains furthermore unstable and tumultuous", he said.
"We stand before big challenges and we must receive a high growth level."
"It is no option, it is an order, because where, otherwise, we find work for our millions of young men and women."
